03:44.834 --> 03:47.468
♪♪

03:47.553 --> 03:49.386
(panting)

03:51.192 --> 03:52.574
Amberle, wait up!

03:52.610 --> 03:54.276
Hey, wait!

03:54.328 --> 03:56.445
Last track we picked up
was over a mile ago.

03:56.530 --> 03:57.496
Okay, we need to gain some ground

03:57.581 --> 03:58.697
before her trail goes cold.

03:58.782 --> 03:59.698
We need to rest.

03:59.783 --> 04:01.783
We need to find Eretria.

04:01.835 --> 04:03.001
Amberle, stop.

04:03.087 --> 04:04.336
She thinks we ran off without her

04:04.421 --> 04:05.954
and that she's alone again.

04:06.040 --> 04:07.756
And I'm not gonna let that happen!

04:07.791 --> 04:09.708
- Why are you yelling?
- I don't know!

04:11.262 --> 04:12.427
You feel guilty.

04:12.463 --> 04:13.545
I get it.

04:13.631 --> 04:14.963
So do I.

04:15.015 --> 04:16.714
But we can't get distracted.

04:16.800 --> 04:18.517
We have a job to do here.

04:18.601 --> 04:19.767
How can you even say that?

04:19.803 --> 04:21.519
You're the one always
saying we can't let our

04:21.605 --> 04:23.805
feelings get in the way of our mission.

04:23.857 --> 04:25.691
You need to rest, Amberle.

04:25.776 --> 04:29.394
I'll rest after I find Eretria.

04:29.480 --> 04:30.445
Stop!

04:35.486 --> 04:36.485
Probably Trolls.

04:37.788 --> 04:40.122
Eretria told me to
expect traps out here.

04:45.496 --> 04:47.412
(bird squawking)

04:49.750 --> 04:52.501
I will do anything to find her.

04:52.586 --> 04:54.720
But if we want to make it
out of these woods alive,

04:54.805 --> 04:56.471
we need to be careful.

04:56.507 --> 04:59.424
We rest, then we eat.

04:59.510 --> 05:00.842
And then...

05:00.894 --> 05:02.261
then we keep looking.

05:20.864 --> 05:23.448
(door closing)

05:23.534 --> 05:26.118
It's fading.

05:26.203 --> 05:28.503
So fast.

05:28.539 --> 05:30.255
Yes.

05:30.341 --> 05:32.874
That is why I need to
know what you remember.

05:34.461 --> 05:37.462
You were in the presence
of a powerful evil,

05:37.548 --> 05:40.382
fighting for your life.

05:40.467 --> 05:43.802
That kind of darkness,
it can follow you.

05:44.855 --> 05:47.306
I understand your concern, I do,

05:47.391 --> 05:49.391
but I'm okay.

05:54.898 --> 05:56.064
Who did that?

05:57.735 --> 05:58.984
You.

06:01.455 --> 06:02.988
Your gift is powerful.

06:03.073 --> 06:04.239
But now that Dagda Mor knows,

06:04.291 --> 06:08.243
he will stop at nothing
to own your soul.

06:08.329 --> 06:09.995
I was nearly your age

06:10.080 --> 06:12.964
when my mentor, Bremen, discovered me.

06:13.050 --> 06:16.802
Alone and afraid...

06:16.887 --> 06:19.254
abandoned by my parents.

06:19.306 --> 06:22.257
The Druid trained me in
the ways of the Order.

06:23.894 --> 06:27.095
He gave me purpose and control.

06:28.148 --> 06:31.933
And now it is my turn to do the same.

06:33.237 --> 06:34.603
I believe you

06:34.688 --> 06:36.855
to be the next Druid, Bandon.

06:42.279 --> 06:43.912
A Druid?

06:46.116 --> 06:48.283
And what if I don't want that?

06:48.335 --> 06:52.037
The choice is no longer yours to make.

06:52.122 --> 06:54.289
Without training, you
won't stand a chance

06:54.341 --> 06:58.293
of surviving the Darkness
that is about to descend.

06:58.379 --> 07:02.130
♪♪

07:06.603 --> 07:10.472
(whimpering)

07:22.403 --> 07:23.318
(gasping)

08:01.658 --> 08:03.191
(floor creaking)

08:12.286 --> 08:14.202
Pie?

08:14.254 --> 08:16.838
- It's actually pretty delicious...
- Stop it right there!

08:16.874 --> 08:19.007
Or I will kill you.

08:19.042 --> 08:22.377
A simple "no thanks" would be fine.

08:22.463 --> 08:23.378
You're not a prisoner.

08:23.464 --> 08:25.881
You can leave anytime you want.

08:25.966 --> 08:28.517
But you bought me as a slave.

08:28.552 --> 08:30.302
Okay, I understand how this might be

08:30.387 --> 08:31.636
a little confusing for you,

08:31.722 --> 08:34.722
but I only bought you

08:34.775 --> 08:36.725
to save you.

08:36.809 --> 08:38.559
From the Elf Hunters.

08:38.611 --> 08:40.111
I don't believe you.

08:40.197 --> 08:41.897
I don't blame you.

08:41.982 --> 08:44.783
The world out there is ugly,

08:44.868 --> 08:46.818
and trusting someone equals death.

08:46.904 --> 08:49.120
I get it.

08:49.206 --> 08:51.573
My friends'll be looking for me.

08:51.658 --> 08:52.657
We were separated.

08:52.743 --> 08:56.378
Okay, then I'll get a
search party together.

08:58.549 --> 09:01.917
Now, I managed to stop the infection,

09:02.002 --> 09:03.718
but you lost a lot of blood.

09:03.754 --> 09:05.670
You need to rest, heal.

09:05.756 --> 09:06.755
The Wilderun is no place for you

09:06.807 --> 09:08.173
to be running around alone.

09:08.258 --> 09:10.175
I can take care of myself.

09:10.260 --> 09:12.093
I don't doubt that for a second.

09:12.145 --> 09:14.429
But not in your condition.

09:19.653 --> 09:23.405
♪♪

09:25.075 --> 09:28.276
What are they anyway?

09:28.328 --> 09:30.245
The Sentinels mark the border
between the known world

09:30.280 --> 09:33.164
and the Wilderun.

09:33.250 --> 09:34.699
The point of no return.

09:34.785 --> 09:36.952
Wow, that's encouraging.

09:37.004 --> 09:38.086
The Elvin Royal Family
commissioned them

09:38.121 --> 09:40.005
after the first War of the Races.

09:40.090 --> 09:42.340
A "gift" to the Four Lands.

09:42.426 --> 09:45.544
A symbol of our newly born unity.

09:45.629 --> 09:47.295
But now?

09:47.347 --> 09:49.681
Now I know they're more than a border.

09:49.766 --> 09:52.684
They're a warning not
to cross the Elves.

09:52.769 --> 09:56.137
Look, the Elves have
certainly made mistakes,

09:57.274 --> 09:58.773
but what we're doing...

09:58.809 --> 10:02.060
this isn't about saving any one race.

10:02.145 --> 10:04.529
This is for every one of us.

10:04.615 --> 10:07.532
And I think we all deserve saving.

10:07.618 --> 10:09.117
I hope you're right.

10:12.706 --> 10:15.540
And...

10:15.626 --> 10:18.410
I want you to know I'm
sorry about Pykon.

10:18.495 --> 10:19.961
That I kissed you like that.

10:19.997 --> 10:21.663
It...

10:21.748 --> 10:23.882
I thought you were dead
and then you ran in

10:23.967 --> 10:25.634
and I was so relieved, it was...

10:25.669 --> 10:27.085
Amazing.

10:27.170 --> 10:29.421
Not Pykon, obviously.

10:29.506 --> 10:31.840
That was... insane.

10:31.892 --> 10:34.175
I mean the kiss.

10:34.227 --> 10:37.262
Because that kiss...

10:37.347 --> 10:39.848
That was nothing to be sorry for.

10:39.900 --> 10:41.016
Wil, It's like you said,

10:41.101 --> 10:44.185
we can't let our
feelings get in the way.

10:44.237 --> 10:46.104
Just so we're clear...

10:46.189 --> 10:48.690
my feelings aren't "in the way."

10:48.775 --> 10:51.693
My feelings for you are
what keeps me going.

10:58.619 --> 11:02.170
♪ My love ♪

11:02.205 --> 11:05.373
♪ You know my love ♪

11:07.794 --> 11:09.628
♪ Let it grow ♪

11:11.715 --> 11:14.516
♪ So we can watch it burn ♪

11:18.138 --> 11:21.890
♪ Your love ♪

11:21.942 --> 11:24.726
♪ I know your love ♪

11:27.447 --> 11:29.230
♪ Let it grow ♪

11:31.568 --> 11:34.402
♪ So we can watch it burn ♪

11:38.041 --> 11:41.209
♪ Blue ♪

11:43.046 --> 11:46.214
♪ Blue ♪

11:48.001 --> 11:51.086
♪ Blue ♪

11:52.923 --> 11:56.891
♪ Blue ♪

11:56.927 --> 11:57.976
(thudding in the distance)

11:58.061 --> 11:59.394
(man groaning)

12:07.854 --> 12:11.606
♪♪

12:12.859 --> 12:15.577
(rattling)

12:15.612 --> 12:16.745
Come on.

12:22.035 --> 12:24.536
Fancy meeting you here.

12:24.621 --> 12:28.289
♪♪

12:33.552 --> 12:35.168
Elf Hunters, huh?

12:35.220 --> 12:36.553
Do you know anything, or not?

12:36.638 --> 12:38.004
Of course, I do.

12:38.090 --> 12:40.840
If it's Elf Hunters, I
know where they trade.

12:40.926 --> 12:42.175
He's lying!

12:42.261 --> 12:44.811
He doesn't know where Eretria
is anymore than we do.

12:44.846 --> 12:46.313
We're wasting our time here.

12:46.348 --> 12:47.814
Oh, what?

12:47.849 --> 12:50.400
You're gonna leave me here
to be gutted by Trolls?

12:50.485 --> 12:52.485
As a matter of fact, I would.

12:52.521 --> 12:54.654
You deserve to die alone in a cage

12:54.690 --> 12:56.356
like the dirty animal you are.

12:56.408 --> 12:57.908
(grunting)

12:57.993 --> 12:59.075
Harsh.

12:59.161 --> 13:00.610
You cut the line at Pykon.

13:00.696 --> 13:02.028
You left us to die!

13:02.114 --> 13:04.164
It looks like you made out okay.

13:04.199 --> 13:05.248
No thanks to you.

13:05.334 --> 13:07.200
Let's go.

13:07.252 --> 13:10.704
Hey, Mongrel, how far you
think you're gonna get

13:10.756 --> 13:12.038
before some Troll picks up

13:12.124 --> 13:16.042
the scent of your pretty princess, huh?

13:16.128 --> 13:17.544
I can smell her sweetness from here.

13:17.629 --> 13:19.179
♪♪

13:19.214 --> 13:20.430
Hey, hey!

13:20.515 --> 13:22.882
(grunting)

13:22.968 --> 13:23.967
Do it!

13:24.052 --> 13:25.552
It beats getting eaten by Trolls.

13:25.604 --> 13:26.970
Come on!

13:30.609 --> 13:32.392
Or let me loose

13:32.444 --> 13:35.645
and I'll take you straight to Eretria.

13:35.731 --> 13:37.647
Do you swear you know where she is?

13:37.733 --> 13:40.233
Cross my cold, black heart.

13:40.319 --> 13:41.901
And I always keep my word.

13:43.905 --> 13:46.740
You can't be serious?

13:46.792 --> 13:48.541
You think this is some coincidence?

13:48.577 --> 13:50.543
He's probably been
tracking us for hours.

13:52.214 --> 13:54.581
About a day now.

13:54.666 --> 13:57.083
Can you really blame me?

13:57.135 --> 13:59.719
After seeing what those
Elfstones of yours can do?

14:01.473 --> 14:02.839
If we set him free,

14:02.924 --> 14:04.224
then we deserve whatever
it is he does to us.

14:04.259 --> 14:06.092
Wil, if you have a
better idea, short of us

14:06.144 --> 14:07.677
wandering through Troll
territory all night,

14:07.763 --> 14:10.063
I'm all ears.

14:10.098 --> 14:13.733
She certainly is.

14:13.769 --> 14:15.819
Clearly we can't trust him.

14:15.904 --> 14:17.320
But with someone who
actually knows these woods,

14:17.406 --> 14:19.189
we actually stand a chance
of finding Eretria.

14:27.199 --> 14:30.950
We were taught Humans were warmongers,

14:31.036 --> 14:34.788
intent on destroying the world.

14:34.873 --> 14:36.790
But Human-kind was more than that.

14:36.875 --> 14:39.542
It was curious and compassionate,

14:39.628 --> 14:41.428
brilliant even.

14:41.463 --> 14:43.129
I mean, we built great glass cites

14:43.215 --> 14:46.549
and machines that allowed
us to travel to the stars.

14:48.553 --> 14:51.054
Sounds like a bedtime story.

14:51.139 --> 14:53.723
No, that is what the Elves
want us to believe.

14:53.809 --> 14:56.609
What you see here is the
first of many colonies,

14:56.645 --> 14:58.478
Human colonies, all coming together

14:58.530 --> 15:01.481
to usher in a new era of man.

15:01.566 --> 15:04.234
Human, Troll, Elf, Gnome.

15:04.319 --> 15:06.152
They're all animals.

15:06.238 --> 15:07.987
And reading books and baking pies

15:08.040 --> 15:10.206
isn't gonna keep anyone safe.

15:10.292 --> 15:13.293
Yeah, you're right.

15:13.328 --> 15:14.744
Follow me.

15:20.669 --> 15:22.552
So, when we settled here,

15:22.637 --> 15:24.003
we were overrun by Trolls.

15:24.089 --> 15:26.589
We lost half our people
in the first night.

15:26.675 --> 15:27.674
Women, children.

15:27.759 --> 15:29.142
It was a bloodletting.

15:29.177 --> 15:30.677
Then why stay?

15:30.762 --> 15:32.512
I was tired of running.

15:32.597 --> 15:34.347
And I saw a future here.

15:34.399 --> 15:36.182
One that could be negotiated.

15:36.234 --> 15:37.901
With the Trolls?

15:37.986 --> 15:41.187
Well, our truce is tentative at best.

15:41.273 --> 15:44.774
Keeping us alive requires
more than just... hope.

15:50.115 --> 15:51.831
What is it?

15:51.867 --> 15:53.867
They called it a gun.

15:53.919 --> 15:56.369
I bought a couple off an old tracker.

15:56.455 --> 15:58.838
Cost me an entire harvest of corn.

15:58.874 --> 16:00.123
(gun cocking)

16:06.014 --> 16:07.964
It was worth every kernel.

16:08.049 --> 16:09.349
Here.

16:14.856 --> 16:18.358
Now, pull that hammer back,

16:18.393 --> 16:21.561
focus on the little line.

16:21.646 --> 16:23.863
Point it straight at the target

16:23.899 --> 16:26.983
and, uh... squeeze.

16:43.168 --> 16:44.384
Well...

16:44.419 --> 16:45.885
if I had ten of you around,

16:45.921 --> 16:48.171
those Trolls would not stand a chance.

16:55.931 --> 16:57.931
Cross us again...

16:57.983 --> 17:00.099
and I'll gut you like
the pig that you are.

17:16.167 --> 17:17.784
Looks like we have a deal.

17:22.257 --> 17:24.174
What's so special about this map?

17:24.259 --> 17:25.842
Apparently, the key to saving the world

17:25.926 --> 17:28.928
from Demons lies there, in Safehold.

17:28.964 --> 17:30.263
Look, I know it sounds crazy

17:30.298 --> 17:31.714
but if you'd seen half
of what I've seen,

17:31.800 --> 17:32.765
you'd believe me.

17:32.801 --> 17:33.933
It doesn't sound crazy.

17:33.969 --> 17:36.052
No more than man landing on the moon.

17:36.137 --> 17:39.472
Like that really happened.

17:39.524 --> 17:42.475
Look, all I wanted was
my life to be my own.

17:42.527 --> 17:44.561
To be free.

17:44.646 --> 17:47.146
Turns out "fate" has a
twisted sense of humor.

17:49.234 --> 17:51.451
I need to find my friends.

17:51.486 --> 17:54.153
And when I do, we need
to get to Safehold.

17:58.827 --> 18:01.828
Well, I've sent trackers
to the Old World.

18:01.880 --> 18:05.715
And this, uh, map of yours?

18:05.800 --> 18:08.718
I've lost three men in that same spot.

18:08.803 --> 18:10.470
Only one ever made it back.

18:10.505 --> 18:13.089
Hebel... and he's never been the same.

18:13.174 --> 18:14.674
The man with the melted face?

18:14.759 --> 18:17.260
Yeah, we met.

18:17.345 --> 18:20.179
Look, I don't know what's ahead,

18:20.265 --> 18:23.483
but I know I need to get there.

18:23.518 --> 18:25.351
Well, then you should go.

18:27.656 --> 18:29.906
But before you do...

18:29.991 --> 18:31.491
I want you to see something.

18:36.531 --> 18:40.199
♪♪

18:54.015 --> 18:55.214
Your Highness.

18:59.387 --> 19:00.470
You're drunk.

19:04.392 --> 19:06.142
So you are magic.

19:09.397 --> 19:12.031
- Your Highness...
- No, don't call me that.

19:12.067 --> 19:14.200
This is not my path.

19:14.235 --> 19:15.485
Never was.

19:15.570 --> 19:18.655
I didn't want it then and
I don't want it now.

19:18.740 --> 19:21.207
You are the heir.

19:21.242 --> 19:23.326
- You must...
- Abdicate the throne to Kael

19:23.411 --> 19:25.378
and the Council tonight at the eulogy.

19:25.413 --> 19:27.714
I strongly advise against it.

19:27.749 --> 19:29.582
Why?

19:29.634 --> 19:31.301
Counselor Kael battled fearlessly

19:31.386 --> 19:34.304
alongside my father in the last war.

19:34.389 --> 19:37.223
She's far better suited for
what lies ahead than I.

19:37.258 --> 19:40.893
Kael Pindanon hid behind
the walls of Arborlon,

19:40.929 --> 19:42.512
trembling with fear

19:42.597 --> 19:46.399
as your father fought
alongside Shea Ohmsford.

19:46.434 --> 19:48.017
They defeated the Warlock Lord.

19:48.103 --> 19:51.404
Them and them alone!

19:51.439 --> 19:52.438
Oh, good.

19:53.658 --> 19:56.442
Yet another story I can
never hope to live up to.

19:59.748 --> 20:02.115
Is this what you want?

20:02.167 --> 20:05.118
To be known as the drunken fool

20:05.170 --> 20:07.787
who forfeited the crown.

20:07.839 --> 20:10.590
It's what's best for Arborlon.

20:10.625 --> 20:11.591
(chalice clattering)

20:15.013 --> 20:18.548
You can walk away from
your duty if you wish,

20:18.633 --> 20:21.684
but do not pretend

20:21.770 --> 20:24.303
that it's noble or brave.

20:27.559 --> 20:29.142
♪♪

20:33.911 --> 20:37.646
(distant chattering)

20:43.221 --> 20:45.188
This is where they brought Eretria?

20:51.113 --> 20:53.780
All right, let's get her.

20:53.865 --> 20:55.448
Easy, tough guy.

20:55.534 --> 20:57.033
What? This place?

20:57.069 --> 20:59.486
I've done business with these people

20:59.571 --> 21:01.237
and something's not quiet right.

21:01.323 --> 21:05.241
Then what exactly is our plan?

21:05.327 --> 21:08.411
Your big plan isn't exactly my problem.

21:08.463 --> 21:10.246
Shocking turn of events.

21:10.332 --> 21:12.248
Oh, Wil, come on.

21:14.836 --> 21:16.586
Don't forget to hide your ears.

21:16.671 --> 21:18.088
Wait, you're leaving us?

21:22.978 --> 21:24.511
(hissing)

21:28.734 --> 21:30.767
What is this, a party?

21:30.819 --> 21:34.437
Yeah, and I want you to do the honors.

21:34.523 --> 21:36.022
I don't understand.

21:36.108 --> 21:37.941
Oh, you will in a second.

21:42.114 --> 21:44.114
Go ahead, pull it down.

21:50.789 --> 21:54.457
(all cheering)

22:05.720 --> 22:07.020
What's going on?

22:07.105 --> 22:09.055
Surprise isn't over yet.

22:13.445 --> 22:15.612
Tye.

22:15.647 --> 22:17.113
We need to find someone else.

22:17.149 --> 22:18.615
But, Tye, it's tonight, we...

22:18.650 --> 22:21.067
We need to find someone else.

22:28.877 --> 22:32.829
♪♪

22:49.598 --> 22:52.065
A toast!

22:52.150 --> 22:55.018
To the incredible progress
we've made here...

22:55.103 --> 22:56.352
(woman) Here, here!

22:56.404 --> 22:59.689
...sown with our own hands and hearts,

22:59.774 --> 23:01.024
working side by side

23:01.109 --> 23:03.443
in pursuit of a better
future for Humans.

23:03.528 --> 23:05.161
(all cheering)

23:05.197 --> 23:08.364
We should be proud of
what we've done here.

23:08.450 --> 23:09.282
Especially...

23:09.367 --> 23:11.868
this exceptional apple brandy!

23:11.920 --> 23:14.204
(crowd chuckling)

23:14.289 --> 23:17.874
Now tonight there will be music.

23:17.959 --> 23:19.626
And dancing.

23:19.711 --> 23:21.461
And more if you're lucky.

23:21.546 --> 23:23.346
(crowd chuckling)

23:23.381 --> 23:27.350
But first... a brief
glimpse at our future.

23:27.385 --> 23:29.219
Something to inspire us all.

23:29.304 --> 23:33.022
It is a vision of the life
we will build together.

23:33.058 --> 23:35.692
Of the life our ancestors
had before the War.

23:45.987 --> 23:47.987
(all) Yeah!

23:48.073 --> 23:49.122
<i>Sit down.</i>

23:49.207 --> 23:50.156
<i>If you are referring to...</i>

23:50.242 --> 23:52.075
(man) Boo, Elf!

23:52.127 --> 23:53.626
<i>You are correct.</i>

23:53.712 --> 23:56.963
<i>The Kolinahr is also a
discipline you broke...</i>

23:57.048 --> 23:58.331
<i>to join us.</i>

23:58.416 --> 24:01.050
<i>On Vulcan I began sensing
a consciousness...</i>

24:01.086 --> 24:04.921
So what do you think?

24:05.006 --> 24:06.589
It's magic.

24:06.675 --> 24:07.640
No.

24:07.726 --> 24:09.058
It's Man.

24:11.229 --> 24:12.929
<i>I believe it made...</i>

24:15.517 --> 24:19.269
♪♪

24:21.773 --> 24:25.441
(all cheering)

24:26.828 --> 24:30.580
(dance music blaring)

25:02.814 --> 25:03.947
(door opening)

25:03.982 --> 25:06.866
Stop right there!

25:06.952 --> 25:09.485
What's your business here?

25:09.571 --> 25:11.955
We're Elf Hunters.

25:11.990 --> 25:15.041
We heard we might be
able to trade here.

25:15.126 --> 25:17.410
Then I'm afraid we have quite
a situation, don't we?

25:19.998 --> 25:21.331
Just look at those rags.

25:21.383 --> 25:22.966
You can't wear those to a party.

25:23.001 --> 25:24.167
Here.

25:24.219 --> 25:25.301
Find yourselves something fun to wear

25:25.337 --> 25:27.587
and join the party, okay?

25:32.677 --> 25:33.810
(sighing)

25:37.899 --> 25:39.515
Come on, let's get dressed.

25:43.355 --> 25:45.271
Wil, your Elfstones pouch, it's gone.

25:45.357 --> 25:47.490
I know. Cephalo stole it.

25:47.525 --> 25:49.192
Come on, we don't have that much time.

25:57.202 --> 26:00.870
Like taking candy from a baby.

26:00.955 --> 26:04.707
♪♪

26:16.938 --> 26:18.054
Sleep tight, sweetie.

26:18.139 --> 26:19.355
(muffled shouting)

26:21.076 --> 26:24.661
(dance music blaring)

26:36.227 --> 26:37.393
Let's split up and look for her.

26:37.429 --> 26:39.012
We'll meet back at the tree line.

27:00.585 --> 27:01.785
Have your scouts returned?

27:01.870 --> 27:02.877
I'm sorry?

27:03.003 --> 27:05.229
Your scouts, have they
found my friends?

27:05.290 --> 27:06.256
Not yet.

27:07.876 --> 27:09.876
Is it possible your
friends kept moving?

27:09.961 --> 27:12.128
Headed to this Safehold without you?

27:14.683 --> 27:17.300
Listen...

27:17.352 --> 27:20.804
You can tell me to mind
my own business but...

27:20.889 --> 27:23.523
can you explain why you're doing this?

27:23.608 --> 27:24.974
You'll laugh.

27:25.060 --> 27:26.393
I won't.

27:28.480 --> 27:31.147
It's my destiny.

27:31.233 --> 27:33.817
Well, your "destiny" sounds a lot like

27:33.869 --> 27:36.403
slavery to me, Eretria.

27:36.488 --> 27:38.321
Your friends want you on their quest.

27:38.373 --> 27:41.958
I want you here.

27:41.993 --> 27:44.544
But all that matters...

27:44.629 --> 27:46.162
What is it you want?

27:50.669 --> 27:52.168
What's wrong?

27:55.057 --> 27:57.590
Nothing.

27:57.676 --> 28:00.977
It's just that nobody's
ever asked me that before.

28:01.012 --> 28:02.312
Well...

28:02.347 --> 28:04.180
then you should ask yourself.

28:07.402 --> 28:11.521
Or... you could just dance with me.

28:12.858 --> 28:16.993
<i>♪ This ain't a safe ride home ♪</i>

28:20.782 --> 28:24.617
<i>♪ Not for a girl of your kind ♪</i>

28:28.874 --> 28:32.959
<i>♪ It ain't a place I'd go... ♪</i>

28:37.099 --> 28:40.517
- Hey, watch yourself!
- Sorry.

28:40.552 --> 28:42.385
Like I said, if he's not done with that

28:42.471 --> 28:45.472
Rover bitch by sunrise,
then I'll kill her myself.

28:46.725 --> 28:50.477
♪♪

28:54.983 --> 28:57.951
<i>♪ The city lights fall on our face ♪</i>

28:58.036 --> 28:59.819
Tye.

28:59.905 --> 29:01.454
What's the problem, Frances?

29:01.540 --> 29:02.705
(whispering)

29:05.410 --> 29:07.210
I'll be right back.

29:10.632 --> 29:12.749
Don't go anywhere.

29:18.890 --> 29:22.759
<i>♪ I can't protect us from our fate ♪♪</i>

29:22.844 --> 29:24.394
Wil?

29:24.429 --> 29:25.595
What are you doing here?

29:25.680 --> 29:26.563
We came to rescue you.

29:26.598 --> 29:27.981
But from the look of things,

29:28.066 --> 29:29.682
it doesn't appear you need saving.

29:29.768 --> 29:30.984
You're right, I don't.

29:31.069 --> 29:32.435
I'm okay.

29:32.521 --> 29:34.938
So you decided to go dancing?

29:34.990 --> 29:36.406
Seriously?

29:36.441 --> 29:38.525
Did you forget what we're
supposed to be doing?

29:38.610 --> 29:39.742
Forget?

29:39.778 --> 29:41.110
How could I forget?

29:41.163 --> 29:42.579
You and Amberle have been telling me

29:42.614 --> 29:45.281
what to do ever since we left Arborlon.

29:45.367 --> 29:48.001
Maybe I'm done with that.

29:48.086 --> 29:49.836
Done?

29:49.921 --> 29:52.255
Yeah, I want to lead my own life.

29:52.290 --> 29:54.624
You won't have a life if
we don't get to Safehold.

29:54.709 --> 29:56.125
None of us will.

29:56.211 --> 29:57.377
What's wrong with you?

29:57.462 --> 29:58.294
With me?

29:58.380 --> 29:59.462
Oh, thank goodness.

29:59.514 --> 30:00.713
Okay, we need to get out of here now.

30:00.799 --> 30:01.764
She's right.

30:01.800 --> 30:04.467
She's always right, isn't she?

30:04.553 --> 30:05.518
What's going on?

30:05.604 --> 30:06.936
Well, when it comes to this quest,

30:06.972 --> 30:08.805
you two have made your choice.

30:08.890 --> 30:11.224
But I didn't.

30:11.309 --> 30:12.976
I've done my part.

30:13.028 --> 30:15.228
Now I'm staying here.

30:15.313 --> 30:17.981
With my own kind.

30:18.033 --> 30:19.782
Then I'm staying, too.

30:19.818 --> 30:21.201
- What?
- What?

30:21.286 --> 30:23.036
I'm not leaving here without Eretria.

30:23.121 --> 30:25.121
Look, the Ellcrys revealed you to me.

30:25.156 --> 30:26.322
Okay, you're part of this, part of us.

30:26.374 --> 30:28.208
You're confused, Princess.

30:28.293 --> 30:29.542
I was in this just to earn some coin.

30:29.628 --> 30:31.127
No, you weren't. Eretria...

30:31.162 --> 30:32.912
You came here for the map.

30:32.998 --> 30:33.963
Not for me.

30:33.999 --> 30:36.833
What map?

30:36.885 --> 30:38.585
The map to Safehold.

30:41.673 --> 30:43.339
Now, why don't you
fill your boyfriend in

30:43.391 --> 30:46.092
while I go get the map?

30:46.177 --> 30:48.394
I'll meet you outside in five minutes.

30:48.480 --> 30:50.730
And if we refuse to leave?

30:50.815 --> 30:53.349
Then I'll tell every
Human in here about you.

30:53.435 --> 30:55.151
And your pointy ears.

30:58.773 --> 31:00.189
(dance music blaring)

31:00.242 --> 31:02.191
- You didn't tell me about a map.
- I'm sorry.

31:02.244 --> 31:03.826
In all the insanity,
I must have forgot.

31:03.862 --> 31:06.112
Is that why you were so
desperate to find her?

31:06.197 --> 31:07.163
Because of this map?

31:07.198 --> 31:08.748
What? No!

31:08.833 --> 31:10.199
Are you sure?

31:10.285 --> 31:11.701
How can you say that?

31:11.753 --> 31:14.170
What kind of heartless
monster do you think I am?

31:14.205 --> 31:15.672
To us.

31:15.707 --> 31:17.040
To Humans.

31:17.125 --> 31:19.626
Cheers!

31:19.711 --> 31:23.463
♪♪

31:25.383 --> 31:27.850
You must be Eretria's friends.

31:36.672 --> 31:38.338
It is said that a warrior

31:38.390 --> 31:41.174
who dies fearlessly in battle

31:41.226 --> 31:43.477
will reap many rewards
in the afterlife.

31:47.516 --> 31:49.766
If that is true...

31:49.852 --> 31:53.320
then my father and
brother will stand tall

31:53.355 --> 31:55.489
before the Holy Mountain...

31:55.524 --> 31:57.024
the richest of men.

31:59.862 --> 32:02.279
And it is time for me to make
a sacrifice in their honor.

32:04.700 --> 32:07.034
One that I've discussed
with Counselor Kael.

32:09.371 --> 32:11.004
I will give...

32:16.261 --> 32:18.378
(groaning)

32:18.430 --> 32:19.796
(groaning)

32:28.390 --> 32:31.808
I will give my solemn vow...

32:31.894 --> 32:35.195
to battle bravely in the
name of the Four Lands.

32:36.732 --> 32:39.282
The Demons are coming for us.

32:39.368 --> 32:42.235
And we will not back down.

32:42.287 --> 32:43.904
I will fight with you

32:43.989 --> 32:47.707
and beside you... as your king!

32:58.420 --> 33:01.421
All hail the king.

33:01.507 --> 33:03.056
(all) All hail the king!

33:07.146 --> 33:08.728
All hail the king.

33:32.004 --> 33:33.920
(man) Eretria.

33:37.709 --> 33:39.376
How do you know my name?

33:42.464 --> 33:44.047
Your friends are in danger.

33:46.635 --> 33:49.219
What do you know about my friends?

33:49.304 --> 33:51.471
Don't trust him.

33:51.523 --> 33:53.306
Who? Tye?

33:53.392 --> 33:54.558
(groaning)

33:54.643 --> 33:56.810
Let me go, you...

33:56.895 --> 33:59.479
Your body is the vessel,

33:59.565 --> 34:01.815
your blood is the key.

34:01.900 --> 34:03.817
Don't let them leave without you.

34:21.420 --> 34:22.835
I was looking for you.

34:24.672 --> 34:26.672
I said to wait in the barn...

34:26.757 --> 34:27.974
with the others.

34:28.010 --> 34:30.760
You did?

34:30.846 --> 34:32.145
Okay, you caught me.

34:35.067 --> 34:37.684
I thought maybe we could
finish what we started.

34:39.188 --> 34:42.239
You sure that's what you want?

34:42.324 --> 34:43.857
Definitely.

34:48.246 --> 34:51.998
(moaning)

35:08.684 --> 35:10.016
(gun cocking)

35:12.054 --> 35:14.554
Have you done something to my friends?

35:14.606 --> 35:17.974
Utopia's peace has its price.

35:18.060 --> 35:19.192
The Trolls demand a toll each month.

35:19.228 --> 35:21.861
And your friends?

35:21.897 --> 35:23.313
They're going to pay it...

35:23.398 --> 35:25.398
so you don't have to.

35:25.484 --> 35:27.734
So you weren't saving me.

35:27.786 --> 35:29.119
You were going to... what?

35:29.204 --> 35:31.788
Sacrifice me to some damn Troll?

35:31.873 --> 35:33.573
No, that was before I knew you.

35:33.625 --> 35:35.375
Well, in that case...

35:35.410 --> 35:38.161
You belong here, Eretria.

35:38.247 --> 35:40.130
With us.

35:40.215 --> 35:42.749
I'll take my chances with the Trolls.

35:42.801 --> 35:44.467
I can take you to your friends.

35:44.553 --> 35:46.886
Thanks, but...

35:46.922 --> 35:49.506
(groaning)

35:49.591 --> 35:51.224
...I'll find them myself.

35:59.438 --> 36:00.637
You can't leave us out here.

36:00.723 --> 36:01.772
Shut it, Elf.

36:01.807 --> 36:03.940
(howling in the distance)

36:06.645 --> 36:08.312
They're coming.

36:08.364 --> 36:10.314
Who's coming?

36:10.399 --> 36:11.982
The Trolls, Princess.

36:12.067 --> 36:13.400
I told you there was
something not right

36:13.485 --> 36:15.569
about these people, didn't I?

36:15.654 --> 36:18.405
Never thought I'd end up as dinner.

36:18.490 --> 36:20.624
We're being fed to the Trolls?

36:20.659 --> 36:22.826
And now he's up to speed.

36:22.878 --> 36:24.494
I got a proposal for you, Blondie.

36:25.881 --> 36:27.497
In exchange for my freedom.

36:27.583 --> 36:29.800
And what exactly is that?

36:29.835 --> 36:32.085
I'm talking about Elfstones,

36:32.171 --> 36:34.004
the most powerful magic
in all the Four Lands,

36:34.056 --> 36:35.672
the last hope for the Elvin race.

36:35.758 --> 36:37.674
And they could be yours.

36:37.760 --> 36:39.176
I got 'em right in my pocket.

36:39.261 --> 36:40.510
With these, you could
get rid of the Elves,

36:40.562 --> 36:41.845
once and for all.

36:47.519 --> 36:48.518
(scoffing)

36:48.570 --> 36:49.853
Nice try.

36:49.905 --> 36:50.737
What?

36:50.823 --> 36:52.105
Look, the kid must still have 'em.

36:52.191 --> 36:53.407
He switched them on me!

36:53.492 --> 36:54.825
I swear, Check his pockets.

36:54.860 --> 36:55.776
I swear!

36:55.861 --> 36:57.494
Have a nice life, Rover.

36:57.529 --> 37:01.164
Well, for the next 20 seconds anyway.

37:01.200 --> 37:02.616
Let's go.

37:02.701 --> 37:04.668
(growling approaching)

37:04.703 --> 37:06.119
Well, here's a thought...

37:06.205 --> 37:07.921
since you've still got the
real Elfstones on you,

37:08.006 --> 37:09.706
why don't you whip 'em out
and show us what you've got

37:09.792 --> 37:11.091
before that pack of Trolls rolls in

37:11.176 --> 37:12.876
and sucks the meat off our bones!

37:12.928 --> 37:14.378
Even if I could reach them,

37:14.430 --> 37:15.962
they only work on one thing...

37:16.048 --> 37:16.930
Demons.

37:17.015 --> 37:18.849
Would it really hurt to try?

37:18.884 --> 37:21.218
(growling intensifying)

37:21.303 --> 37:22.302
Wil!

37:26.225 --> 37:27.224
Hurry!

37:27.309 --> 37:28.892
I'm trying. I just...

37:28.977 --> 37:31.278
(groaning) I can't reach the Stones!

37:31.363 --> 37:33.563
(growling)

37:33.649 --> 37:35.565
(panting)

37:43.041 --> 37:44.741
- No, no, no, no!
- (gunshot firing)

37:49.214 --> 37:50.380
(sighing)

37:56.505 --> 37:58.755
I'm sorry for what I said.

37:58.807 --> 38:00.223
I'm sorry I ever doubted you.

38:00.259 --> 38:00.754
(clearing throat)

38:01.098 --> 38:02.348
Sorry to spoil the moment,

38:02.433 --> 38:04.099
but a little help here?

38:07.271 --> 38:09.521
Oh, no, no, no!

38:09.607 --> 38:12.191
Do you realize what you've done?

38:12.276 --> 38:13.525
Tye, please...

38:13.577 --> 38:15.110
You've doomed us all!

38:15.196 --> 38:17.162
(gunshots firing)

38:26.340 --> 38:28.424
(groaning)

38:28.509 --> 38:29.708
(Amberle) Wil!

38:35.549 --> 38:37.099
Hey, give me that thing

38:37.184 --> 38:39.218
and I'll hold them off while
you guys make a run for it.

38:39.270 --> 38:41.387
Seriously, do you think
I'm that stupid?

38:41.472 --> 38:45.023
Kid... just you can trust me.

38:45.059 --> 38:48.227
♪♪

38:48.312 --> 38:49.395
I've got nothing to lose.

38:49.447 --> 38:52.398
This whole time... I'm sorry.

38:52.483 --> 38:54.733
I'm sorry I cut the line at Pykon.

38:54.819 --> 38:57.903
I'm sorry for all of it.

38:57.988 --> 38:59.738
You're the best thing I ever did.

38:59.790 --> 39:02.241
Let me make up for it.

39:02.293 --> 39:04.576
Come on.

39:04.628 --> 39:08.580
♪♪

39:09.800 --> 39:12.418
(Amberle) Wil, come on.

39:12.503 --> 39:14.503
Go... go make me proud, kid.

39:14.588 --> 39:15.754
Go save the world.

39:25.649 --> 39:27.099
(trigger clicking)

39:27.184 --> 39:30.936
♪♪

39:38.362 --> 39:40.696
(growling)

39:44.785 --> 39:46.919
(gasping)

39:46.954 --> 39:48.120
(trigger clicking)

39:53.961 --> 39:55.627
Tye, what are you doing?!

39:55.679 --> 39:57.463
Frances...

39:57.548 --> 39:59.264
- No!
- (screaming)

39:59.300 --> 40:00.265
(growling)

40:00.301 --> 40:02.134
No!

40:02.186 --> 40:03.135
(groaning)

40:06.807 --> 40:08.223
(panting)

40:11.278 --> 40:13.395
Now what?

40:13.481 --> 40:14.958
Now we find Safehold.

40:21.322 --> 40:25.073
♪♪

